51:14.205 --> 51:17.106
that when she found out
what happened at the party...

51:17.108 --> 51:20.076
Luce swore he wouldn't tell
what happened at the party.

51:20.078 --> 51:22.178
I thought he didn't know
what happened.

51:24.382 --> 51:25.414
I should go.

51:25.416 --> 51:27.283
No, wait.
Stephanie, please.

51:27.285 --> 51:29.051
Listen to me.

51:29.053 --> 51:32.521
I just want to know
the truth, Okay?

51:32.523 --> 51:35.791
Now, if Ms. Wilson made you
feel like whatever happened

51:35.793 --> 51:39.061
should be some kind of
a political statement,

51:39.063 --> 51:40.596
then that's wrong of her.

51:40.598 --> 51:44.100
As women what we need to do
is support each other.

51:44.102 --> 51:45.201
Do you understand?

51:47.038 --> 51:48.270
I'm not sure.

51:48.272 --> 51:50.406
I want to support you.

51:50.408 --> 51:52.341
You deserve to be supported.

51:57.048 --> 51:58.047
Okay.

52:02.386 --> 52:05.421
But for me to do that
I need to know what happened.

52:05.423 --> 52:08.257
It's easy to say that.

52:08.259 --> 52:11.794
But once you know something,
you can't un-know it.

52:11.796 --> 52:14.497
I want to know,
no matter what.

52:16.067 --> 52:17.333
Please.

52:23.407 --> 52:27.209
[crickets chirping]

52:31.282 --> 52:33.048
[engine cuts]

52:37.355 --> 52:40.789
Harriet, please...

52:40.791 --> 52:43.826
I'm sorry. I can't think of
any other way to resolve this.

52:43.828 --> 52:47.029
You suffer from
a condition, Ro.

52:47.031 --> 52:50.032
And it's clear my home is no
longer an ideal environment.

52:50.034 --> 52:51.534
You sound like
one of them doctors

52:51.536 --> 52:52.868
she about to
dump me with again.

52:52.870 --> 52:55.337
I'm not dumping you.
Oh really?

52:55.339 --> 52:56.906
That's what it
feels like, Harriet!

52:59.143 --> 53:00.809
[whimpers]
Come on, now.

53:00.811 --> 53:03.045
Don't make a scene.
Don't make a scene.

53:03.047 --> 53:04.847
Harriet!

53:06.284 --> 53:07.616
Ro...
It's fine.

53:07.618 --> 53:09.218
It's fine, it's fine...

53:09.220 --> 53:10.452
It's fine!

53:20.064 --> 53:23.899
Harriet!
[whimpering]

53:28.506 --> 53:30.039
Orlicki had a party.

53:32.810 --> 53:34.376
I was drunk.

53:34.378 --> 53:36.745
I had gone with two friends.
All three of us were drunk.

53:36.747 --> 53:39.181
Please don't tell anyone
this, it's embarrassing.

53:39.183 --> 53:42.218
No, no, this is between us.
I promise.

53:43.854 --> 53:49.024
People kept having shots of
stuff that tasted like syrup

53:49.026 --> 53:52.995
and I just kept drinking it
because it was easy

53:52.997 --> 53:55.731
but I got dizzy.

53:56.734 --> 53:58.334
I lost my friends.

54:00.204 --> 54:02.938
Orlicki found me and told me
to go lie down in the basement.

54:05.176 --> 54:07.076
It was dark.

54:07.078 --> 54:08.611
I couldn't see.

54:10.214 --> 54:11.780
I felt my way
over to the couch

54:11.782 --> 54:13.682
but there were
people there.

54:15.753 --> 54:18.587
Next, someone said we should
play the Santa Claus game.

54:18.589 --> 54:19.588
What's that?

54:20.791 --> 54:24.226
It's this stupid game
that guys play

54:24.228 --> 54:27.229
where a girl gets passed
around from lap to lap

54:27.231 --> 54:29.131
and depending on how far
she lets them go

54:29.133 --> 54:31.467
or how much they like you
sitting on them,

54:31.469 --> 54:33.702
they rate you
from one to three.

54:33.704 --> 54:34.970
Ho ho hos.

54:34.972 --> 54:36.538
My God, that can't be real.

54:37.908 --> 54:39.275
There are worse games.

54:40.911 --> 54:41.877
Anyway,

54:43.247 --> 54:44.980
they started
passing me around.

54:46.317 --> 54:49.618
I kept thinking,
"God,

54:49.620 --> 54:51.820
what if I throw up
right now?

54:51.822 --> 54:53.722
How embarrassing
would that be?"

54:55.993 --> 54:58.527
When they started,
they were laughing.

54:59.563 --> 55:01.330
But the longer
it went on...

55:03.067 --> 55:07.202
And it felt like
it went on forever.

55:09.407 --> 55:12.975
All I could hear
was breathing.

55:15.179 --> 55:17.079
Breathing,

55:17.081 --> 55:19.915
and counting.

55:19.917 --> 55:22.051
One, two,

55:23.254 --> 55:24.920
two,

55:24.922 --> 55:26.088
three...

55:26.991 --> 55:29.858
One, two...

55:31.128 --> 55:32.127
At some point

55:32.129 --> 55:33.495
I definitely said

55:33.497 --> 55:34.963
I wanted them to stop.

55:34.965 --> 55:37.132
But maybe it sounded
like I was joking

55:37.134 --> 55:40.336
or maybe it was just something
I said to myself in my head...

55:42.373 --> 55:46.075
There were hands
everywhere.

55:48.379 --> 55:50.746
It was like
they were swallowing me.

55:53.884 --> 55:56.385
And sometimes
in their laps

55:58.022 --> 56:01.256
I could feel...
[sniffles]

56:02.693 --> 56:04.093
Oh!
[sniffling]

56:04.962 --> 56:05.928
Oh.

56:07.465 --> 56:08.897
Gross.
[nervous chuckle]

56:11.969 --> 56:13.502
Um.

56:13.504 --> 56:17.072
When I woke up,
Luce was there.

56:17.074 --> 56:19.007
He said he found them
and told them to stop.

56:19.009 --> 56:20.509
[laughs nervously]

56:20.511 --> 56:22.778
And he stayed with me
the rest of the night.

56:25.549 --> 56:27.249
Is it possible that...?

56:28.853 --> 56:30.152
Was Luce one of the guys?

56:30.154 --> 56:31.987
He wouldn't do that.

56:31.989 --> 56:33.655
But he...
He just wouldn't.

56:39.497 --> 56:40.996
What happened
with Ms. Wilson?

56:42.533 --> 56:45.100
There were
a lot of rumors.

56:46.704 --> 56:48.370
It was
at the same time

56:48.372 --> 56:50.205
Deshaun Meeks got
kicked off the team

56:50.207 --> 56:53.242
because Wilson found
weed in his locker.

56:53.244 --> 56:56.578
She searched
Deshaun's locker?

56:56.580 --> 56:58.514
And called
the cops.

56:58.516 --> 57:01.583
I didn't want that.
What would I say?

57:01.585 --> 57:03.118
I couldn't
remember anything

57:03.120 --> 57:07.089
and I definitely didn't tell
everyone I was drunk.

57:07.091 --> 57:08.257
What did Luce say?

57:09.360 --> 57:12.261
He said I was right
not to tell.

57:13.631 --> 57:15.898
Because he was protecting
his friends.

57:15.900 --> 57:17.733
Because he was
protecting me.

57:17.735 --> 57:20.436
He didn't want me to do
anything I didn't want to do.

57:25.876 --> 57:27.309
Why did you two break up?

57:28.746 --> 57:29.778
I don't know.

57:31.615 --> 57:32.848
I miss him.

57:34.251 --> 57:36.351
He's the best boyfriend
I ever had.

57:40.458 --> 57:41.490
[sniffles]

57:43.761 --> 57:45.127
Stephanie...

57:46.330 --> 57:48.497
I'm really sorry
for what happened.

57:48.499 --> 57:49.498
Don't be.

57:49.500 --> 57:50.499
[chuckles]

57:52.002 --> 57:53.402
Everything is fine now.

57:54.905 --> 57:57.506
[inaudible]

57:59.910 --> 58:02.344
[inaudible]

58:15.092 --> 58:20.729
[tense droning]

58:25.202 --> 58:27.736
[keys jangle]

58:31.509 --> 58:33.442
Hey!
Hey.

58:37.948 --> 58:39.114
Where were you?

58:40.117 --> 58:41.917
Emergency patient.

58:42.786 --> 58:44.286
Oh, really?

58:49.360 --> 58:50.359
[kiss]

58:54.832 --> 58:57.065
Karen seems good.
Yeah, she is.

58:58.302 --> 58:59.568
They're happy.

59:00.571 --> 59:02.838
The baby fidgets.

59:02.840 --> 59:05.874
Mm-hm. I think that's
just a baby thing.

59:07.578 --> 59:09.411
[Amy giggles]

59:10.514 --> 59:11.747
Are you drunk?

59:11.749 --> 59:13.048
[Peter chuckles]

59:15.352 --> 59:19.187
So you don't think it's
that baby in particular.

59:19.189 --> 59:20.222
How would I know?

59:21.492 --> 59:23.592
I mean,
I don't know, so...

59:24.328 --> 59:26.028
how would I know?

59:26.030 --> 59:27.095
Yeah.

59:27.831 --> 59:29.331
PETER: Right?

59:29.333 --> 59:32.434
Mm, yeah,
I guess you wouldn't.

59:32.436 --> 59:33.669
PETER:
No.

59:34.939 --> 59:37.372
AMY:
You know, it's not Luce's fault

59:37.374 --> 59:39.575
you were denied diaper
changing privileges.

59:39.577 --> 59:41.810
No.
[chuckles]

59:44.214 --> 59:45.914
Thanks.

59:45.916 --> 59:47.549
Look, we made a choice.

59:47.551 --> 59:50.419
I'm okay with that as long
as you recognize it cost us.

59:51.355 --> 59:52.421
Which means?

59:53.691 --> 59:56.291
I did want something
different once.

59:56.293 --> 59:57.859
Ten years and
you're trapped.

59:58.562 --> 01:00:00.095
Your words.

01:00:00.097 --> 01:00:02.631
Well, you said it.
You wanted something different.

01:00:02.633 --> 01:00:05.233
I did, yeah.
Like what?

01:00:05.235 --> 01:00:09.104
Look, I'm proud of our son.

01:00:10.541 --> 01:00:13.809
Okay, I love him.
I love him

01:00:13.811 --> 01:00:17.212
more than I'll ever
understand, okay?

01:00:17.214 --> 01:00:20.415
But we spent years
with him in therapy

01:00:20.417 --> 01:00:22.217
and rehabilitation.

01:00:22.219 --> 01:00:23.752
Our friends
couldn't understand

01:00:23.754 --> 01:00:26.622
why we didn't just
have a kid of our own.

01:00:26.624 --> 01:00:28.256
And so while they
fell away doing

01:00:28.258 --> 01:00:31.493
what normal
fucking people do,

01:00:31.495 --> 01:00:33.962
we worked our asses off
to give him a life,

01:00:33.964 --> 01:00:37.432
at the expense of our own.
So to pretend that

01:00:37.434 --> 01:00:39.267
that didn't
cost us anything

01:00:39.269 --> 01:00:40.636
is bullshit.
I wasn't pretending.

01:00:40.638 --> 01:00:43.138
You are!
Amy.

01:00:44.842 --> 01:00:45.841
You are.

01:00:46.944 --> 01:00:49.177
You want so
desperately for him

01:00:49.179 --> 01:00:50.912
to be what you want him to be,
you're ignoring

01:00:50.914 --> 01:00:52.781
what's right
in front of you.

01:00:52.783 --> 01:00:54.149
What he is, is

01:00:55.119 --> 01:00:57.319
our son.
Right.

01:00:57.321 --> 01:00:59.087
And nothing's going
to change that.

01:01:00.124 --> 01:01:01.256
Right.

01:01:03.260 --> 01:01:04.393
So...

01:01:06.263 --> 01:01:07.329
fuck this.

01:01:07.331 --> 01:01:08.664
Fuck you.

01:01:12.936 --> 01:01:15.404
[¶¶¶]

01:01:19.176 --> 01:01:20.542
[sighs]

01:01:23.814 --> 01:01:25.013
I came here

01:01:25.849 --> 01:01:27.849
to America,

01:01:27.851 --> 01:01:29.418
to this school,

01:01:30.988 --> 01:01:32.387
and I found myself.

01:01:36.727 --> 01:01:39.695
When I first met my mother,
she couldn't pronounce my name.

01:01:41.131 --> 01:01:44.566
She tried over and over
to get the emphasis

01:01:44.568 --> 01:01:47.402
on the syllables
correct, but...

01:01:47.404 --> 01:01:48.637
she just couldn't.

01:01:51.341 --> 01:01:54.042
So my father suggested
that they rename me.

01:02:02.820 --> 01:02:04.886
They picked Luce,

01:02:04.888 --> 01:02:06.154
and, uh...

01:02:10.260 --> 01:02:12.360
[breath trembles]

01:02:12.362 --> 01:02:14.529
I thought about that
when I was figuring out

01:02:14.531 --> 01:02:16.331
what to say
to you all tonight.

01:02:18.902 --> 01:02:21.903
And I realized how lucky
I am to be an American.

01:02:25.342 --> 01:02:27.509
Because here I got
the chance to start over.

01:02:29.279 --> 01:02:30.979
To redefine myself.

01:02:33.183 --> 01:02:35.484
Here we can be who we choose.
Here...

01:02:40.290 --> 01:02:44.659
[somber low strings]

01:03:11.221 --> 01:03:14.990
[heavy breathing]
[bed knocking]

01:03:14.992 --> 01:03:17.726
[knocking continues]

01:03:19.730 --> 01:03:22.964
[sighs]

01:03:29.673 --> 01:03:32.541
Remember that fish
we got him for his birthday?

01:03:37.681 --> 01:03:40.282
Dennis.
Yeah, that's right.

01:03:40.284 --> 01:03:42.818
Yeah. Poor Dennis.

01:03:44.955 --> 01:03:47.989
Yeah. The way he just
pulled him out

01:03:47.991 --> 01:03:50.525
and threw him across
the room like that.

01:03:50.527 --> 01:03:52.894
Like a piece
of deli meat.

01:03:55.098 --> 01:03:57.232
"I just wanted
to see him fly, mom."

01:04:03.841 --> 01:04:05.740
We didn't screw up,
did we?

01:04:08.512 --> 01:04:09.611
No.

01:04:12.516 --> 01:04:14.049
Everything's fine.

01:04:15.452 --> 01:04:17.552
[¶¶¶]

01:04:17.554 --> 01:04:20.121
[Peter and Amy
talking indistinctly]

01:04:22.226 --> 01:04:24.059
[cell phone chimes]

01:04:27.698 --> 01:04:30.232
[typing]

01:04:49.152 --> 01:04:50.485
[phone clicks off]

01:04:52.556 --> 01:04:55.323
[school bell rings]

01:04:59.029 --> 01:05:03.265
So, what does it mean
to speak in code?

01:05:03.267 --> 01:05:06.334
Well, it tells you about
a particular group.

01:05:06.336 --> 01:05:08.403
The necessity to have
a shared vocabulary.

01:05:08.405 --> 01:05:09.604
[door opens]
LUCE: Sorry.

01:05:12.242 --> 01:05:17.112
To have common struggles
in a society.

01:05:17.114 --> 01:05:19.014
You see,
language is a bond.

01:05:19.016 --> 01:05:21.182
It's how we tell each other
apart, but more importantly,

01:05:21.184 --> 01:05:22.550
it's how we stick together.

01:05:22.552 --> 01:05:24.619
[knock at door]
Excuse me, Ms. Wilson,

01:05:24.621 --> 01:05:26.421
I need you to come
with me please.

01:05:26.423 --> 01:05:27.656
Right now.

01:05:28.926 --> 01:05:31.793
[murmuring]

01:05:34.398 --> 01:05:37.699
[commotion grows louder]

01:05:39.436 --> 01:05:41.803
ROSE: Where's my sister?

01:05:41.805 --> 01:05:43.471
She works here. She is here.

01:05:43.473 --> 01:05:44.873
Rosemary!
Where's my sister?

01:05:44.875 --> 01:05:49.144
Rosemary! I'm right here.
I'm right here.

01:05:49.146 --> 01:05:50.478
